Hello there. 

This is a port of the famous map zm_dust_world from CS 1.6. This port is not in its final stage yet.
Many things are not perfect like the scaling/placement of textures or usage of brushes but neither was the original map. The map is definitely ready to play and looks decent enough, imo. I plan to make a final version with the things listed above fixed and some more decals and maybe some props too.

HISTORY UPDATES

= Surf_Zoomboys by Sid =

It's time for you to prove yourself. Smooth strafes. Close cuts. Hit the ramps like you've never hit them before. Are you truly a zoomy boy? Find out on Surf_Zoomboys!

The ramps are large and the jumps are long and low. The obstacles are very few but don't relax, being skilled at maintaining speed and optimizing jumps is a must in order to reach the end zone. While the theme is pleasant to look at, this map is all about the surf. Are you skilled enough to break the sub-minute milestone?

- Tier 3 Linear
- 2 Bonuses

A happy bday map for Sacred, a person who kept skillsurf alive by managing KSF community for many, many years. 
Who knows if we'd even have half the skillsurf maps we have now if it wasn't for his persistence, who knows if skillsurf would've even made it to the "mainstream" in csgo if it wasnt for him. All that's certain is that he's still here after all this time and is making it possible :)
The themes of stages on this map are based on Sacred's maps (calamity2, nemesis, elysium, calibration), as well as one bonus is based on his past (maybe even current) favorite map, surf_exile.
Tier is maybe 4-5 idk.

notices:
- bonus 1 boost is too weak if you try to play it on Momentum Mod, it works in CSS just fine,
- the map is not considered to be ported to other Source Engine games, if you want to do that, then decompile the map (or ask masog for .vmf), take the assets from the .bsp and work it out yourself (just a note that the map is only possible to be compiled with -notjunc, as it exceeds the T-Junctions limit).

surf_treasurehunt is a t1 lineair surf map.

It was originally an attempt to make a lineair surf give different paths/skips, and this has been reflected in the skips that are possible.

It took about a month worth of time working at the map, originally sticking with self-crafted ramps in Hammer to details and environment, switching to Blender ramps and overall making the map more enjoyable to surf by adding a ton of skips. While I might not be a good visual designer, I do priorize making the surf enjoyable and as smooth as possible. I learned a lot of using Blender and implemented some of those elements in the map. The main map contains 0 teleport triggers, same for the bonusses.

In addition it has 2 bonuses: One is a previous sketch of the map, focusing around a single skip.

The second one is an mix of surf_treespam and surf_royal made easy.

Triggers have been added in order to make the starting/end zones.

Map tested and played with default Momentum Mod values, so unless you want to get launched keep the default values.
Credits:

Kompile (https://www.youtube.com/user/SDKompile) for making a video about creating ramps in Blender and the Blender plugin SURGE which allows for very simple Blender ramp creation.

Momentum Mod community for any questions regarding Source Hammer I had.

surf_sluice for inspiration for the sewer part

surf_treespam and surf_royal for bonus 2

This map will be ported to CS:GO soon, but since it was developed in CSS/Momentum Mod this is the main release.

Hello,

This is a map I started well over a year ago. I took a break from hammer for awhile, and I didn't have any plans to return to mapping at the time. But since my schedule started cooling down, I decided to come back to finish this.

This is a 2 staged map that combines surf and bhop. The original idea was inspired by sinsane2 b3. I wanted to make a much easier version of that, but design it to where you keep your speed between each section. It's pretty confusing, so I would recommend watching a replay of the map before trying it out.

The map contains 4 bonuses. Bonus 4 was made last minute, and there's no teleporter to get to it. In this bonus there's a single ramp, which you loop until you have enough speed to get to the end.

Due to the fact that you can prehop sections as much as you want, this map is a little hard to tier. But I'd say it's around tier 3.

surf_summer

By Hardex and Tioga060 

Sponsored by Fnatic, and with additional work from Juxtapo, Guadalupe, Mark C. and not_a_zombie. Surf_summer is a map published under the newly formed level design team, JSurf Studios, which is led by Hardex and Tioga060.

Welcome to the sun-soaked bliss that is surf_summer. In this map you’ll get to experience everything you’d want out of the perfect summer. From a trip to the beach, to a skatepark, to a waterpark, and even deep sea diving, we’ve got it all. 

At tier 2 difficulty, surf_summer is a map designed for beginner surfers, but we also had experienced surfers in mind! They will have a fun time discovering all of the shortcuts and optimizing their route to perfect a speed run through the map. 

When Fnatic contacted us to create this project, we knew we had to come up with exciting ways to promote their new summer product line, so the map comes with an in-game reward system that will let you unlock different player models for progressing through the map. 

The map also has lots of easter eggs to discover, so look closely as you surf!

The map includes awesome artwork from Ferry Gouw, a graphic designer most widely known for his work with Major Lazer. OWSLA has agreed to let us use their music in the project, so check out the groovy soundtrack throughout the map!



Note: surf_summer_ksf is a much lighter version created for KSF CS Source servers. It is about 200mb less than the complete port.

= Surf_School_Fix by Sid =

Surf_School was originally a commissioned map, but over the past year it has been added to many servers on CS:GO, and was initially released with some issues overlooked. Now the fixed version is available for Source!

With the intent to be a training grounds, each stage is progressively harder, and introduces newer players to the type of obstacles they will encounter in skill surf. Using a hybrid layout, each stage can be tackled individually, or you can carry your speed from the previous stage to compete for the fastest time.

- Tier 1 Staged/Linear, 10 stages
- Bunnyhop Bonus (Originally planned for Surf_Beverages!)

!! IMPORTANT !! Auto-bunnyhop must be enabled for the best experience!

CSGO Version: https://gamebanana.com/maps/209298

This map was made for the KSF spring mapping contest 2020 in 20 days total.

The contest's theme was 'sunnyhappylove' - with that in mind, you start off by leaving your office after your working hours and go through various outside and inside areas that resemble a range of free time activities or/and are nature themed.

The map is designed as a staged linear map / linear map with checkpoints.

It features six stages, but there are multiple routes to complete this map in a linear fashion.

Each route varies in difficulty as can be seen in the three linked videos below this post.

The goal was to offer experienced surfers multiple shortcut possibilities that vary in difficulty, but also give more casual surfers a good chance at beating the map.

Tier (based on a stage-by-stage completion): 3

Stages: 6

Bonuses: 1

Important: the map is intended to be played with sv_maxvelocity set to 5000 (or more since you do not reach 5000 anyway on 66 tick)


Important2: the map is compiled with HDR lighting only - turn HDR on or it will be fullbright

Here are showcases of three different routes, depending on your experience you can combine / leave out different skips that are shown in the videos - or maybe find new ones?
